<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900628-0041</DOCNO><DOCID>900628-0041.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Rogers Corp.:   Loss Seen for 2nd Quarter,   Reflecting $7 Million Charge</HL><DATE>06/28/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ROG</CO><LP>   Rogers Corp. said it will take a second-quarter pretaxcharge of about $7 million and will post a loss for thequarter and the full year.   The Rogers, Conn.-based maker of electronic parts said itis taking several steps to reduce costs and improve profitmargins, including selected divestitures and a &quot;significant&quot;reduction in salaried payroll through terminations andearly-retirement offers.</LP><TEXT>   In last year's second quarter, Rogers had net income of$386,000, or 13 cents a share, on sales of $43 million. Forthe year, the company had net of $1.6 million, or 53 cents ashare, on sales of $175 million.   Norman L. Greenman, president of Rogers, said that&quot;savings from the actions taken are projected to recover theentire amount of the one-time charge within two years.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>